[2] USA: Funding gap affecting disease research
Date: 14 Jan 2015
Source: WSJ [edited]
http://blogs.wsj.com/pharmalot/2015/01/14/nih-chief-loses-sleep-that-u-s-researchers-may-leave-for-china/ [edited]


USA National Institute of Health chief loses sleep that US researchers may leave for China
-------------------------------------------------------------------
The flat budgets Congress has doled out to the NIH [National Institute of Health] in recent years, combined with the effects of inflation, mean the agency's "purchasing power" has fallen by 25 percent since 2003, [Francis Collins stated in a speech] to the [JP Morgan Healthcare conference reported 14 Jan 2015]... - more

[It is disappointing that Congress does not recognize the need to increase its support of NIH after observing the emergence and spread of such lethal diseases as Ebola, of course, but also West Nile, dengue, chikungunya, avian influenza, and neglected tropical diseases. Pathogen emergence may occur with little recognition of the threat they pose; thus we must be vigilant in maintaining our research programs in the USA to be prepared basically for what is inevitable. See [1] above re unpredictability of Ebola, for one. - Mod.LK]

