15 Jan 2015 Sierra Leone: The international Red Cross says a local employee has died of Ebola in Sierra Leone, becoming the 1st Red Cross worker or volunteer to succumb to the disease there. The International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies said the male nurse, whom it didn't identify, worked at an Ebola treatment center in Kenema. He died Tue [13 Jan 2015] and was confirmed to have been suffering from the disease. It said it is investigating how the man became infected and whether it happened at home or at work. The agency said 29 people who had contact with him are being monitored for symptoms.
